In a responsive drive to ensure that Kogi State comes out of the current quagmire amidst the COVID 19 pandemic, Kogi State governor, Alhaji Yahaya Bello, yesterday inaugurated the Kogi team for the World Bank assisted programme. The programme is aimed at designing and preparing  the State CARES  Program- with emphasis on the mode of coordination and delivery system and to factor out the key activities and expenditure/ budget programme relating to the kogi needs for results. In his inaugural speech, the governor who was represented his deputy, Chief Edward Onoja, noted that the Nigeria CARES programme of the World Bank must be optimised by Kogi State and charged the team to deliver their responsibility with all commitment for the benefits of the states. He however congratulated the members whom he said were selected based on competence, experience and character as well urge them to justify the confidence reposed in them. Earlier at the Banquate Hall of the Government House, venue of the ceremony, the secretary to the government of Kogi State, Dr Folashade Ayoade Arike, listed the objectives of the programme to include: to protect livelihood and food security of poor and vulnerable families in kogi state and as facilitates recovery of local economic activity through SME. The SSG also gave the names of the nine members of the Committee as recommended by the World Bank to include: Asiwaju Asiru Idris, state commissioner for Finance, Budget & Economic Planning as the State Team Leader; Oneal Ejigbo   Daniel      – commissioner for Rural Development, member, Yakubu Mohammed     – secretary MSME, member; Mr Paul Ogunmola, FADAMA Coordinator, member; Adamu Shaidu Obansa, RAMP Coordinator, member; Dr Noah Alilu         – YESSO Coordinator, member; Abdulrasaq Falilat, head, Cash Transfer, member; Prince Onyekehi Abdulkareem, head, SIP, member and Momoh Dauda, GM CSDP,    member. In his response after the inauguration, the  Kogi State CARES team leader , Hon Asiru Idris assured the governor of the readiness of the committee to deliver according to mandate.